llman.md has been updated successfully.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"ec1acdcf-f33e-4912-afb1-d14db8676411\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-09T19:17:50.933Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/alisha/.claude/plans/bright-soaring-ullman.md\",\"oldString\":\"# Fix E2E (and agent-integration) Plugin Subcommand Visibility\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe `/e2e` skill works (auto-discovered from `.claude/skills/e2e/SKILL.md`), but subcommands like `/e2e:debug`, `/e2e:triage-ci`, `/e2e:implement` are invisible. They're defined as plugin commands in `.claude/plugins/e2e/commands/`, but local project plugins aren't auto-discovered — only marketplace-installed plugins get loaded.\\n\\nThe `agent-integration` plugin has the same problem.\\n\\nThe original plan's Step 1 (`/plugin marketplace add ./.claude/plugins/e2e`) failed because each individual plugin directory isn't a marketplace — a marketplace is a **container** with a `marketplace.json` that lists plugins.\\n\\n## Approach: Create a local marketplace wrapping both plugins\\n\\nA marketplace needs a `.claude-plugin/marketplace.json` file that catalogs plugins with relative source paths. We'll make `.claude/plugins/` itself a marketplace containing both plugins, then register it via `extraKnownMarketplaces` + `enabledPlugins` in `.claude/settings.json` so it's automatic for all team members.\\n\\n## Steps\\n\\n### 1. Create marketplace.json\\n\\nCreate `.claude/plugins/.claude-plugin/marketplace.json`:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"entire-dev-tools\\\",\\n  \\\"owner\\\": {\\n    \\\"name\\\": \\\"Entire Team\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"plugins\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"e2e\\\",\\n      \\\"source\\\": \\\"./e2e\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"E2E test triage, debugging, and fix implementation toolkit\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"agent-integration\\\",\\n      \\\"source\\\": \\\"./agent-integration\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Multi-phase toolkit for integrating a new AI coding agent with the Entire CLI\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Key**: The `source` paths are relative to the marketplace root (`.claude/plugins/`), pointing to the existing plugin directories.\\n\\n### 2. Register the marketplace in `.claude/settings.json`\\n\\nAdd `extraKnownMarketplaces` and `enabledPlugins` to the existing project settings file:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"extraKnownMarketplaces\\\": {\\n    \\\"entire-dev-tools\\\": {\\n      \\\"source\\\": {\\n        \\\"source\\\": \\\"local\\\",\\n        \\\"path\\\": \\\"./.claude/plugins\\\"\\n      }\\n    }\\n  },\\n  \\\"enabledPlugins\\\": {\\n    \\\"e2e@entire-dev-tools\\\": true,\\n    \\\"agent-integration@entire-dev-tools\\\": true\\n  },\\n  // ... existing hooks, permissions ...\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Note**: The `extraKnownMarketplaces` entry makes the marketplace known to Claude Code. The `enabledPlugins` entries auto-install both plugins with project scope so all team members get them.\\n\\n### 3. Run the marketplace add + install commands\\n\\nAfter creating the files, run these commands interactively to install the plugins:\\n\\n```\\n/plugin marketplace add ./.claude/plugins\\n/plugin install e2e@entire-dev-tools --scope project\\n/plugin install agent-integration@entire-dev-tools --scope project\\n```\\n\\nThe `--scope project` flag writes to `.claude/settings.json`, which is checked into the repo.\\n\\n### 4. Verify plugin structure is correct\\n\\nThe existing plugin structures already follow the correct pattern:\\n\\n```\\n.claude/plugins/                          <- marketplace root\\n├── .claude-plugin/\\n│   └── marketplace.json                  <- NEW: marketplace catalog\\n├── e2e/\\n│   ├── .claude-plugin/plugin.json        <- existing\\n│   ├── commands/\\n│   │   ├── debug.md                      <- /e2e:debug\\n│   │   ├── triage-ci.md                  <- /e2e:triage-ci\\n│   │   └── implement.md                  <- /e2e:implement\\n│   └── README.md\\n└── agent-integration/\\n    ├── .claude-plugin/plugin.json        <- existing\\n    ├── commands/\\n    │   ├── research.md                   <- /agent-integration:research\\n    │   ├── write-tests.md                <- /agent-integration:write-tests\\n    │   └── implement.md                  <- /agent-integration:implement\\n    └── README.md\\n```\\n\\nNo changes needed to the existing plugin or command files.\\n\\n## Files to Create/Modify\\n\\n| File | Action | Description |\\n|------|--------|-------------|\\n| `.claude/plugins/.claude-plugin/marketplace.json` | **CREATE** | Marketplace catalog listing both plugins |\\n| `.claude/settings.json` | **MODIFY** | Add `extraKnownMarketplaces` and `enabledPlugins` |\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. After creating the marketplace.json and updating settings.json, run:\\n   ```\\n   /plugin marketplace add ./.claude/plugins\\n   ```\\n2. Then install:\\n   ```\\n   /plugin install e2e@entire-dev-tools --scope project\\n   /plugin install agent-integration@entire-dev-tools --scope project\\n   ```\\n3. Start a new Claude Code session in this project\\n4. Type `/e2e:` and verify tab-completion shows `e2e:debug`, `e2e:triage-ci`, `e2e:implement`\\n5. Run `/e2e:debug` and verify it loads the procedure\\n6. Type `/agent-integration:` and verify `research`, `write-tests`, `implement` appear\\n7. Run `/agent-integration:research` and verify it loads the procedure\\n\\n## Fallback: If local marketplace doesn't work\\n\\nIf the local path marketplace approach has issues (e.g., plugins are copied to cache and lose relative path references to `.claude/skills/`), we'll need to update the command `.md` files to use absolute paths or `$CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR` references. The commands currently reference files like `.claude/skills/e2e/debug.md` — if the plugin is copied to a cache, this relative path won't resolve. In that case, change to:\\n\\n```markdown\\nRead and follow the full procedure from `${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/.claude/skills/e2e/debug.md`.\\n```\",\"newString\":\"# Fix agent-in